<subSubSection pageId="163" pageNumber="442" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="163.[2050,2646,1163,1589]" lastBlockId="163.[1437,2643,1595,2575]" pageId="163" pageNumber="442">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weksler, Percequillo &amp; Voss" authorityYear="2006" box="[2055,2207,1320,1353]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Oreoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="163" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Oreoryzomys</taxonomicName>
is sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1917" box="[2371,2541,1320,1353]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="163" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microryzomys</taxonomicName>
in molecular-based phylogenies; both genera are morphologically similar, suggesting that the former could be a junior synonym of the latter. A single record from El Chiral, El Oro (Ecuador), in the western slope of the Andes is pending taxonomic review for determineits true identity. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1439,2202,1635,1668]" pageId="163" pageNumber="442" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761455" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6761455" box="[1439,2202,1635,1668]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761455/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="442" startId="163.[1439,1611,1635,1668]" targetBox="[1436,2028,1172,1587]" targetPageId="163">
<paragraph blockId="163.[1437,2643,1595,2575]" box="[1439,2202,1635,1668]" pageId="163" pageNumber="442">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1439,1614,1635,1668]" pageId="163" pageNumber="442">Distribution.</emphasis>
